snippet: About 2,000 people are enrolling in private health care plans daily through the state’s website, officials said, a rate that has picked up considerably over the past few weeks.
abstract: California's insurance exchange has enrolled more people than any other state-run exchange and more than the federal exchange serving 36 states, which has been paralyzed by technological failures; officials say about 2,000 people are enrolling in private health plans daily through the state's exchange.
lead_paragraph: About 2,000 people are enrolling in private health care plans daily through the state’s website, officials said, a rate that has picked up considerably over the past few weeks.

headline.main: California Health Exchange Beats All Others in Enrollment, Officials Say
